article.description: David Taylor scored 17 points to lead Pacific past Green Bay 76-58 in the wee hours of Tuesday morning during the 24-hour college basketball marathon.
article.headline: Pacific tops Green Bay 76-58 in wee hours of morning
article.linkText: Pacific tops Green Bay 76-58 in wee hours of morning
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- David Taylor scored 17 points to lead Pacific past Green Bay 76-58 in the wee hours of Tuesday morning during the 24-hour college basketball marathon. T.J. Wallace added 16 for the Tigers (1-1). Ray Bowles (10 points, 11 rebounds) and Sami Eleraky (10 points, 10 rebounds) each had double-doubles. Pacific used an 11-0 run with under nine minutes left in the game to pull away. Trevor Anderson scored 14 points and Khalil Small had 13 for Green Bay, the defending Horizon League tournament champion. The Phoenix (1-1) led 27-26 at halftime but shot just 30 percent from the field and finished 5 of 22 from three-point range. Pacific had a 61-38 advantage on the boards.
